14/03/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Acting President Ljupco Jordanovski signed a decree Friday (12 March) appointing General Gjorgji Bojadziev as the new chief of the army's general staff. 
The appointment had been approved by the late President Boris Trajkovski. 
Bojadziev replaces General Metodi Stamboliski, whose mandate expired on 1 March. 
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 13/03/04)
